<Link id="l00861" /><CodeLine lineNumber="861"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// In the per-module summary, it summarizes the byte offset applied to each</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1135"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Global variable summary information to aid decisions and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1136"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// implementation of importing.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1137"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1138"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Global variable summary has two extra flag, telling if it is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1139"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// readonly or writeonly. Both readonly and writeonly variables</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1143"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// by means of internalizing such variables after ThinLTO import.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1158"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// purely by non-volatile load instructions. This in turn means</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1174"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// are also internalized.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1175" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/globalvarsummary/gvarflags/#af005b1da67090d23f2588f627cab672b"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/globalvarsummary/gvarflags/#af005b1da67090d23f2588f627cab672b">Constant</a> : 1;</span></CodeLine>
